title: For Sale:  Winchester 88 (.308)
postcontent: A classic old Winchester. The Winchester Model 88 was ahead of its time. There is no doubt it was an innovative design that melded power, accuracy, aesthetics and firepower into an almost ideal single rifle. The Model 88 was a completely new design in lever actions. It has no visible hammer; the bolt rotates when operated by the lever, locking up with three lugs just aft of the chamber similar to a bolt action. It feeds from a 4-shot detachable box magazine. Its 22" barrel has a featherweight profile leading to the rifle’s 7 1/4-lb. weight. Cartridges eject from the side, allowing a scope to be mounted center over the bore. Winchesters marketing guys even called it the “bolt action rifle with a lever.”Chambered in popular .308Sling mountsDOM: 1963Factory tapped for a scopeIn excellent condition
